PLANNER RUN SUMMARY
slug: full-stack-developer-python-fastapi
date: 2026-06-14

---

DEMO DECISION
Chosen concept: "Compliance Reconciliation Console" — merges D1 (streaming XML parser) and D3 (rules engine + anomaly dashboard) into one self-contained static demo. D2 (tenant isolation) is addressed in proposal prose only; it is an architecture story, not a clickable artifact.

Rationale: The client's highest-anxiety questions are (1) can you parse 500+ MB XML without OOM, and (2) do you understand the rules-engine + drill-down pattern. This demo makes both tangible before the client spends a euro. It also pre-answers the Milestone 2 payment gate (R17: iterparse PoC with memory profile), which is the single highest-risk decision point in the client's procurement process.

---

PROTOTYPE vs FULL
Decision: LEAN FULL
- No backend integration required (all client-side with sample fixtures + generated data)
- File count stays under 12
- Real parse loop, real rule evaluation, real pagination logic -- not static imagery
- mw-backend: NOT needed

The one honest stub: the demo does not literally stream a 500 MB file in-browser (that is a server-side concern). It simulates the iterparse algorithmic approach with chunked processing, contrasting constant-memory streaming against a naive full-load baseline as record count climbs. The cover letter states this honestly and commits to the real Milestone 2 deliverable.

---

HERO FEATURE
Streaming-parse + reconciliation rules engine with drill-down (R2 + R4 + R17 + Q1)
User selects a seeded fiscal XML fixture; the console runs a simulated streaming parse with a live memory-stability readout (streaming vs naive-load comparison), then evaluates 8-12 representative reconciliation rules (with configurable thresholds) and drills down to offending source transactions on failure.

SUPPORTING FEATURE 1
Analytical dashboard (R5)
Summary tiles, trend/anomaly chart, paginated table over a 100k-row generated dataset mimicking server-side pagination, CSV export.

SUPPORTING FEATURE 2
File-format detector (R1)
Inspects the chosen file, identifies document type, fiscal period, and schema version, and routes to the correct parser profile before parse begins.

---

TECH APPROACH
Self-contained static app. Single index.html + local assets/. React + htm via CDN (no bundler), styled with michaelwegter.com design tokens (dark gallery aesthetic).

Demo destination: ../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/full-stack-developer-python-fastapi/
Served at: /demos/full-stack-developer-python-fastapi/
Site wiring: workSamples.js registry entry, AppFrame.jsx reused unchanged, Navbar.jsx "Work Samples" link added.

